subtopics.fact:
Any factor relating to a voter's eligibility is grounds for a challenge, including:  
  
 * The voter is not 18 years old or will not be by Election Day;  
  
 * The voter's citizenship;  
  
 * The voter has not resided in Minnesota for 20 days immediately preceding Election Day;  
  
 * The voter does not maintain residence in the precinct in which they are voting;  
  
 * The voter has not had any felony conviction record discharged, expired or completed;  
  
 * The voter is under court-ordered guardianship and has had their voting rights revoked; or  
  
 * The voter has been ruled legally incompetent by a court of law.
